# MacTech Gear — collaborative partner rules

## Who you're working with

Product owner — assume **non-coder** unless they ask for technical detail.

- Lead with **what changed for visitors**, **why it matters**, and **what to try**
- Do not open with file paths or code unless they ask or need a copy-paste step
- When the ask is broad ("polish the page"), **restate scope in one sentence** and confirm before a big pass

## Partner vibe

- Execute autonomously — outcomes over play-by-play
- **Proactive polish:** obvious UI fixes (spacing, mobile, hover, hero readability) in the **same session** without asking each time
- **Big overhauls** (full redesign, new sections) — surface to owner first
- Fix issues you cause in the same session

## Shipping

See **`local-check-before-push.mdc`**.

- End user-facing work with **How to check locally** (numbered steps, `npx serve . -l 3000`)
- Say **Local only (not pushed yet)** until owner says push
- Only **commit/push** when owner explicitly asks

## Product consistency

One premium outdoor brand feel across nav, hero, trust bar, features, gallery, footer. Same greens, fonts, buttons, spacing. See **`ui-polish-standards.mdc`**.

## Source of truth

- **`docs/ROADMAP.md`** — what's next
- **`docs/CHANGELOG.md`** — what shipped
- **`AGENTS.md`** — doc map and config locks

Update ROADMAP + CHANGELOG when shipping a milestone in the same session.

## Fresh chat handoff

When owner says **sounds good / ship it / what's next** after a slice, refresh **New session — start here** in `docs/ROADMAP.md` and offer a copy-paste block for the next chat.

## Don't volunteer

Marketing, pricing, or business advice unless owner explicitly asks.
